data.title: The State of New York
data.meta_description: The year-round beauty of its mountains and lakes exemplifies the character and soul of Warren County.
data.text:
Warren County was named in honor of General Joseph Warren, an American Revolutionary War hero of the Battle of Bunker Hill.

It includes the magnificent Lake George Area, in addition to the cultural hub of the City of Glens Falls and the hometown flair of surrounding Southern Adirondack towns and villages.

Main Industries: The county contains the highest concentrated area of medical manufacturers in New York State, with many medical inventions originating in the county. Tourism is also thriving, with popular destination Lake George drawing thousands of tourists each year.

Education: SUNY Adirondack
